This query uses the `dbpedia-owl` namespace which provides the ontology for DBpedia. The query selects the `?secretary` and `?college` variables and returns all individuals (`?secretary`) who are of the type `dbpedia-owl:SecretaryOfTheTreasury`, and their `dbpedia-owl:almaMater` (college). Here is a SPARQL query that you can use to find the past colleges of all secretaries of the Treasury:

```PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
